# InkLex — AI rules

Full briefing: `docs/ai/WORKING-RULES.md`.

## Product

Vocabulary app (InkLex): word cards, folders, statuses `new` | `learning` | `known`, CSV import. Design: Vocabulary Desk from reverso-mvp-design-options.html.

## Stack

- Frontend: React + Vite + TS → `src/`
- Data: Firebase Firestore (client SDK) — collections `words`, `folders`
- **Local DB:** mocked `localStorage` (`VITE_USE_MOCK_DB=true`). No Firebase/emulator network.
- **Prod/Preview:** real `VITE_FIREBASE_*` on Vercel; mock/emulator flags must be off
- Legacy Next API in `backend/` is optional / deprecated for local experiments
- Env: see `.env.example`

## UX (critical)

- Sidebar: **All** + **+**; no folder bullets; inline create/rename; name limit **50** chars; errors **below input**; Esc / blur = cancel
- Mobile: burger → folder drawer (backdrop / Esc / × close)
- Content: **Cards / Learning / Known** tabs above search (counts scoped to active folder)
- **Start Learning**: з All — модал вибору папки; з папки → `/:encodedFolderId/learning` з Learning Hub (контент сторінки: Quest | Review). Quest: new/learning ≤10 (due first, потім rest); Known після 3 correct або drag; `inklex.learningMode`; див. `docs/algorithms/due-first-session.md`
- Folder URL: `/` (All) or `/:encodedFolderId` (base64url folder id; sidebar shows name)
- Card: red **delete** chip on the right
- Drag card → folder (sidebar) or tab (Cards=`new` / Learning / Known)
- Import: on success → close modal + open folder from CSV

## Code

- Minimal diff, existing patterns, CSS variables from `index.css`
- `apiBaseUrl` for all API fetch calls
- User-facing chat responses in **Ukrainian**
- Commits only when explicitly requested
